Chad tried it. We endulged in his nipples.
One last pyramid, with the heavist guy on top. I am a FUCKING hero, BITCHES!

Brewtus"", that shit was so funny when I first read it!

3.04.05 - 3.13.05: Max + Bowling + Bonfire + Miscellaneous
The final song of the final show of Into the Woods! Thank fucking goodness.

So, what happened was- Dirk was trying to eat a shit load of crumbs from a bag, and when he went to scoop them in his mouth, Anglenia being the nice person she is, hit the bag so all the crumbs fell on his face. (Nothing I wouldn't of done too!) Dirk almost died he was caughing so hard, SO FUNNY.
Maximus chillen' in his new backyard.
Maximus, being maximus- chillen' with the tounge out!
Thirsty from all the excitement. Haha. He is so big, he has to lay down to drink out of that water thing. Toby used to not have to move to drink, haha.
WE WENT TO THE BEACH! Woo! After we were all done and stuff, we deicded to get the bonfire going hardcore. This is once we set everything up.
Ryan conquered the fire! Muhahahaha! This shows how tall the fucking fire got!
... and, hell why not some more fire? Good? Good.
Angelina fucking around when we all went to Holdiay bowl. Good times. I did so bad when I bowled that day.
Muhahaha! They thought they were taking a cute picture of this just them two. Hell no. I look funny in the back, haha. Dirk looks lost.
3.11.05: Bringing Max Home!
This is our new dog Max! We got him from the pound, after our neighbor (who works there) told us he is awesome. He is 4 and a half years old, a black lab, and a true playa.
He decided to try and sit shotgun on the way home, and kept panting a lot. Casi took this pic when I was making fun of him.

2.19.05 - 3.04.05: Movie Theatre + Dirk Dance + San Francisco + Into the Woods + Miscellaneous

So, Suzanne was home for the weekend and we hung a bit. Good times, except for when we went outside her house (in the middle of the WOODS) to get a soda. I hate cats and there was a renegade hissing rabbis filled cat gaurding the fridge gargoyle style. Scared the shit out of me.
Suzanne is a savage and will fight anyone at any time. She tried to beat the shit out of Tim, but he whopped her. Haha.
It was cold in Hayward, so Angelina tried to bundle up to stay warm and still talk. It was funny.
Stache was welding some steel together for the Into the Woods set. It was a bright blue, it was sweet.
This is (hardcore) Julie cutting some steel to be welded with a chop saw.
Another angle of my favorite Japense shop worker spinin' some blades.
I have to climb a tall wall-later when I do crew for Into the Woods, and before the Trees were finished, it looked sick from trhe view from up there. This is right before intermetion ends.
This is once the curtain raises. <3 Into the Woods.

You might not know, but my dad is a world famous paralell parker... I got SOME of the genes. This doesnt look good, but I did this in one swift, quick motion up at hayward WITH traffic coming. This is awesome, for me.

This is Janet in the corner.
This is Craig's name in the corner! SO EXCITING!
So, this is College for me. Haha, not to different from IHS. We were writing scripts in 194 and Dirk was trying to joust with some props.

This is when he got REALLY expressive. Haha.

It was so rainy and cloudy this morning, you couldn't even see the top of Warren Hall at Hayward. CRAZY!
<lj-cut text=""2.09.05 - 2.18.05: BART ride + Phallic Symbol + Miscellaneous"">
2.09.05 - 2.18.05: BART ride + Phallic Symbol + Miscellaneous

This was from the BATS handbook. The quote says: ""Freeze games teach people to get laughs by killing stories."" The quote was from Keith Johnstone, the guy who invented current day improv. I have been saying the same thing forever, I felt too cool.
A ""restaurant"" from San Francisco in the middle of two alley ways. It was AWESOME.
My BART train home from leaving Hillary. (I have no idea why I took this picture.)
The way back to San Francisco. (I have no idea why I took this picture too.)
The map inside the train. (I have no idea why I took this picture also.)
My feet on the BART train. (I have no idea why I took this picture as well.)

Who says Starbucks isn't FORCE FEEDING YOU WHAT TO LIKE. Fuck them. Subliminal mind fucking the genereal public into buying thier shit. Joni Mitchell doesn't need their help... she is classic on her own.

Okay, so here is the story. In class (Ancient Theatre), we are reading Lysistrata, a sex filled war play. I have to do this scene with Angelina (below) and I have to rub my ""Phallis"" on her thigh and show her how ""excited"" I am to finally see her. Since we are all immature, we deicded to roll some carpet and use some rubber bands to make me a ""Phallis"" that is up to par, haha. I was very fond of it.

Then, since our class is hella cool- during a previous scene, one of the actors says the word ""dildo"" and Jeff threw it onto the stage. HELLA FUNNY. The professor started hella laughing and twilled it around a bit. <3 college.
Angelina liked it a lot too. Haha.

There is a stop sign by my house that doesn't need to be there- so I just go through it all the time. I always hear there is a cop waiting for people to do that. I see her sometimes. This time I caught her waiting there for people to break the law. Shady! Fuck, Fuck, Fuck da police!
